data analyst \- 2373615


employer: optum services, inc.  



job title: data analyst


location: 1 optum circle., eden prairie, mn 55344 (telecommuting is available from anywhere in the u.s.)


duties: develop and implement a set of techniques or analytics applications to transform raw data into meaningful information using data\-oriented programming languages and visualization software. duties include: perform analysis on large data sets across multiple lines of services and healthcare markets to support strategic decisions and deliver value to the business unit; interpret data and develop recommendations and courses of action through discussions with internal and external stakeholders; ensure data requirements are met during the intake process and identify solutions to resolve issues; evaluate business performance and monitor, track, and report key performance indicators; document processes and identify areas for process improvement; and require an individual to maintain the ability to work in an environment with phi / pii data. telecommuting available from anywhere in the u.s.



requirements: employer will accept a master's degree in business analytics or related field and completion of a university\-level course, research project, internship, or thesis or one year of experience in the job offered or a related analytical occupation. position requires:

* data analysis, statistical modeling, and data visualization such as matplotlib or tableau;
* data ingestion using tools like salesforce and aws s3;
* business analysis;
* sql programming;
* python programming with modules such as pandas, sklearn, or boto3;
* work with clients to plan data workflows, perform qc, perform analytics, share insights and actionable strategies from complex disjointed data sources;


\* data and business processes related to targeting analytics, risk adjustment, and chart retrieval and coding; \* research and developing innovative analytics to generate value;  

* identify trends and opportunities for growth through analysis of complex datasets;
* monitor data quality, validating data pipelines and providing design inputs to build scalable data and analytics processes/data flows;
* distribute big data processing using tools such as aws emr and spark;
* predictive modeling and machine learning models;
* healthcare data processing in accordance with hipaa guidelines;
* workflow orchestration tools such as apache airflow;
* leading data science/analytics projects with cross\-functional teams;
* break down key business deliverables into technical details and implementations;
* communicating complex technical concepts and results to non\-technical stakeholders; and
* utilize databases such as sql server, snowflake, and aws athena.


rate of pay: $116,143 \- $221,382 / per year


